basic grammar ❤️: your = belongs to you you’re = you are their = belongs to them they’re = they are there = a place two = literally a number. 2. too = in addition to something, also to = motion. going to a place. to do something. where = there wear = TO PUT SOMETHING ON YOUR BODY. TO WEAR IT. four = the number. 4. for = POSSESSION. para. in support or favor of something. representing something. fore = THE FRONT OF SOMETHING bare = naked, empty, without something bear = the animal. then = past tense. back then. ok then. than = less than or greater than. used in comparison & contrast. lose = to be without something. to have lost it. loose = wiggly :3, not fixed in place fair = something that is just and without favoritism. or one of the fun thingies like a carnival . or something that is light. fare = like a ticket or sumn. something you pay. die = ️️ cmon guys be fr now dye = coloring something (usually hair or food or slime or sumn) buy = to purchase something by = a preposition. identifying a noun following an action. or identifying an author. bye = goodbye. you should buy bye bye bye by *nsync. hope this helps ❤️ (edited)
